CLEMENT JOHN WAGNER v. MARIE EDITH WAGNER. [No. 27,

April Term, 1934.]

Decided April 27th, 1934.

The cause was argued before Bond, C. J., Pattison, Urner, Adkins, Offutt, Digges, Parke, and Sloan, JJ.

Simon Silverberg, with whom were Silverberg & Silver-berg on the brief, for the appellant. J. Abner Saylor, with whom was. J. Mayer Willen on the brief, for the appellee.

The opinion was delivered

per Curiam.
